  "buggy_files": ["drivers/ata/libata-core.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["ata_device_blacklist"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is missing from the ata_device_blacklist array (line 4393-4617 in libata-core.c), which contains device-specific quirks/horkage flags. The device blacklist is used by ata_dev_blacklisted() (line 4620) to determine which devices have known issues. Samsung SSD 840 (line 4562) and Samsung SSD 850 (line 4564) both have the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag set to disable queued TRIM commands due to timeout issues. The Samsung 860 EVO exhibits identical symptoms (20-30 second lockups, SEND FPDMA QUEUED timeouts) but is not in the blacklist, causing queued TRIM to be attempted on a device that cannot handle it properly. The fix requires adding a Samsung SSD 860* entry to the ata_device_blacklist array with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags, similar to the 840 and 850 entries."
}

